      "surrounding_text": "Many of these universities, especially those in the United States, are systems of individual campuses and may not accurately represent a comparable student body. For example, the enrollment listed for the University of California is the population of the entire student body in the University of California system, which consists of several individual campuses throughout the state. All University of California campuses are referred to as \"The University of California\" and then further identified by the campus location, such as \"University of California, Irvine\". Other states organize their public universities differently, further complicating direct comparisons. a Indicates if most or all students are enrolled in a fully Distance Learning modality",
